parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Stabilitrak system can affect the vehicle's stability and traction control, potentially leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: The "Service Stabilitrak" warning light appears on the dashboard
indicating a problem with the system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the backup camera system can reduce visibility and increase the risk of accidents or injuries when reversing.
symptoms: The infotainment display shows a blue screen with a "camera error" or "service camera system" message instead of displaying the backup camera feed
the backup camera system does not function correctly
the surround camera system does not function correctly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical/electronics system can cause various safety-critical systems to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Driver speedometer screen disappears
center console screen that shows camera information disappears
driver assist package malfunctions
parking brake engages while backing up
vehicle shifts itself into neutral
service safety restraint system and air bag warning lights are illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Driver Assist and Forward Collision System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver assist and forward collision system can cause the system to become unavailable, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Driver assist and forward collision system unavailable
messages appear on the screen
cameras and devices malfunction or fail to function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent system failures can cause unexpected malfunctions, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Intermittent failures of various systems
including driver speedometer screen
center console screen
driver assist package
and parking brake.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Onstar system can lead to a lack of emergency assistance in critical situations, such as accidents, and can also cause inconvenience and frustration due to malfunctioning infotainment and navigation systems.
symptoms: Onstar fails to connect to the vehicle
Onstar light turns red
SRS light comes on
Carplay and Car Internet malfunction
Navigation fails to load
doors lock unexpectedly
Onstar app unable to unlock the car.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the steering system can cause loss of control, leading to accidents, and can also cause driver discomfort and fatigue.
symptoms: Steering wheel is stiffer and heavier when making right turns at speed
steering wheel fights to get back to center when taking right turns
sudden and violent jerking of the wheel to the left
difficulty turning right.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Power Loss and Traction Control/StabiliTrack System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of engine power and failure of the Traction Control/StabiliTrack system can cause unexpected slowing or loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or in hazardous conditions.
symptoms: The Traction Control/StabiliTrack lights come on
the vehicle loses engine power
the vehicle's speed suddenly drops
the vehicle becomes difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Repair and Diagnosis by Dealership
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the dealership to properly diagnose and repair the issue can lead to continued safety risks for the driver and occupants, as well as further damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The dealership clears the error code without resolving the underlying issue
the dealership is unable to replicate the problem
the dealership advises the owner to return the vehicle only when the issue is actively occurring.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning ADAS software can cause the system to incorrectly trigger warnings, which can distract the driver and lead to accidents. The issue can also cause the check engine light to illuminate, potentially leading to unnecessary repairs.
symptoms: The service driver assist warning is displayed on the vehicle's display
the check engine light is illuminated
the ADAS system malfunctions while the vehicle is in motion
the warning reappears after software updates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ineffective software updates can fail to resolve the ADAS issues, leading to continued system malfunctions and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The ADAS software update does not resolve the issue
the warning reappears after the update
the system continues to malfunction despite software updates.
